---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { profile } from '../data/site';

const updated = 'July 14, 2026';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy & cookies"
  description="How this site handles data and cookies — privacy-friendly, EU-hosted analytics used only with your consent."
>
  <section class="scroll-mt-24">
    <div class="wrap max-w-prose pb-16 pt-20 sm:pt-28">
      <p class="label">Privacy</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl leading-tight tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
        Privacy &amp; cookies
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-muted">Last updated {updated}</p>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-[0.98rem] leading-relaxed text-muted">
        <p>
          This is my personal portfolio. I keep data collection to a minimum and I never sell,
          share, or trade your data. There are no advertising cookies and no third-party marketing
          trackers on this site.
        </p>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl leading-tight tracking-tight text-ink">What I collect</h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            If — and only if — you accept in the cookie banner, I use
            <a class="link-underline" href="https://posthog.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PostHog</a>,
            a privacy-friendly, EU-hosted product-analytics tool, to understand how the site is used
            (for example: pages viewed, clicks, and anonymous session recordings of interactions with
            the page). This helps me improve the site. The data is:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2.5">
            {[
              'Pseudonymous — tied to a random id, not to your name or account. There is no login.',
              'Reset daily, so returning visitors are counted fresh rather than tracked over time.',
              'Hosted in the EU and processed only by PostHog as my processor — never sold or shared for ads.',
            ].map((t) => (
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
                <span>{t}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4">
            If you decline, no analytics script is loaded and no analytics cookies are set — nothing
            is tracked at all.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl leading-tight tracking-tight text-ink">The AI assistant</h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            This site has an AI assistant you can chat with to ask about my background. It runs on
            <strong class="text-ink">my own backend</strong> — not a third-party chat service. If you
            choose to use it:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2.5">
            {[
              'Your messages are sent to my backend and routed through an LLM gateway (LiteLLM) to the model providers that generate the reply — currently Google (Gemini) and Mistral AI. Your text is processed by them only to produce an answer.',
              'Your conversation is stored on my backend so the thread survives a reload, with a conversation id kept in your browser to reconnect you to it.',
              'No accounts and no profiling — the assistant only answers questions about me. Conversations are never used for advertising and never sold.',
              'You can delete a conversation at any time. When you do, it is permanently and completely removed from the backend — not archived, not hidden, not kept as a backup.',
            ].map((t) => (
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
                <span>{t}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4">
            The basis for this is providing the feature you chose to use (GDPR Art. 6(1)(b)) — so,
            unlike analytics, it is not gated by the cookie banner.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl leading-tight tracking-tight text-ink">
            Strictly necessary storage
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            A few small values are stored in your browser to make the site work. These are not used
            for tracking and need no consent:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2.5">
            {[
              'Your cookie choice itself, so the banner does not ask again on every visit.',
              'Your light/dark theme preference.',
            ].map((t) => (
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
                <span>{t}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl leading-tight tracking-tight text-ink">
            Your choice &amp; your rights
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            The legal basis for analytics is your consent (GDPR Art. 6(1)(a)). You can change or
            withdraw it at any time via <strong class="text-ink">Cookie settings</strong> in the footer,
            or by clearing this site's data in your browser — withdrawing is as easy as giving consent.
            Under the GDPR you also have the right to access, correct, or erase your data, and to lodge
            a complaint with a supervisory authority.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl leading-tight tracking-tight text-ink">Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            Questions about privacy? Email me at
            <a class="link-underline" href={`mailto:${profile.email}`}>{profile.email}</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-14">
        <a href="/" class="btn">← Back to home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
